
All notable changes to the Terminal Tetris project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

### [v0.3.0] - 29.11.2025

#### Added
- Next piece preview display for strategic planning
- Players can now see upcoming pieces

### [v0.2.0] - 08.11.2025

#### Added
- Authentic NES Tetris scoring system (40/100/300/1200 points)
- Level progression (level up every 10 lines)
- Increasing game speed with each level
- Professional keyboard controls using curses
- Line clearing mechanics with blocks falling down
- Hard drop functionality (spacebar)
- Enhanced terminal rendering with error handling

#### Changed
- Improved game loop for responsive controls
- Enhanced collision detection system
- Better terminal size adaptation

#### Fixed
- Rotation collision detection
- Terminal boundary rendering issues
- Game over detection logic

### [v0.1.0] - 29.10.2025

#### Added
- All 7 classic tetromino shapes (I, O, T, L, J, S, Z)
- Piece rotation system (clockwise/counter-clockwise)
- Collision detection with walls and placed pieces
- Piece locking mechanism
- Basic game loop with automatic gravity
- Professional project structure with GitFlow
- Comprehensive test suite with pytest
- Virtual environment configuration
- Documentation in `/docs/` folder

#### Technical
- Modular architecture (Game, Board, Tetromino classes)
- Test-Driven Development (TDD) approach
- GitFlow workflow implementation
- Pure Python implementation (no external dependencies)

### [Unreleased]

#### Planned Features
- High score system
- Colorful terminal rendering
- Start menu and pause screen
- Sound effects
- Game statistics tracking

---

*For detailed release notes, see the [releases/](releases/) directory.*